posts.name: Robertson Robotics
posts.cooked: To me it feels like you don’t hear much about BaneBots these days.

posts.name: Yiğit
posts.cooked: Oh, those are the wheels cranberry alarm used? I don’t know how I missed that, my bad. yeah, I should’ve included it in the poll, but the majority of “other” votes are probably that then.

Our practice bot is running the original WCP version of those wheels which are 2" wide. We were going to use the WCP but when we saw they went to 1.5" we decided to do the thriftybot wheels for our comp bot. I will say there was issues with the original WCP wheels. The adhesive would release and the hub would just spin, we had to re-glue all of them that we had. When I contacted RC he said they knew about it and revamped the wheel to solve that problem so the new 1.5" should be fine
